	Deface v1.4.1 - Programmed by Ian J. Howle 
		 	
		 	Art & Animation by Alexander F. Perry
		 	
		 	Beta tested by Wendell Watanabe
		 


The object of Deface is to remove all of the tiles. You do so by matching two
tiles on the outer left & right edges of the puzzle. There are four layers of
tiles and the edge tile from one layer can be matched with an edge tile of
another layer.





Software used to develop Deface:

				 Devpac 3 assembler
				 GDS
				 CITAS
				 Brilliance
				 Clarity 16



System requirements: AGA Amiga with 4 megs fast RAM and a DBLNTSC monitor.
		     
		     


